# turborepo instructions (Bun)

Short turborepo usage for automated agents (project uses Bun):

- Use Bun to install dependencies and run package binaries.
- Use Turbo to run tasks across the monorepo (build, dev, lint, test).

Examples (PowerShell):

```
bun install
bunx turbo run build --filter=apps/*
bunx turbo dev --filter=apps/client
bunx turbo run lint test --parallel
```

Notes:
- Use `--filter` to target packages (e.g. `--filter=apps/*` or `--filter=apps/client`).
- Prefer `bunx` or `bun run` to invoke binaries installed in the repo.

Keep commands short and target specific packages when possible.

Install Turbo (if not present):

```
bunx --bun turbo@latest
```

# shadcn instructions

Use the latest version of Shadcn to install new components into the client app. Example (add a button component to the `apps/client` package):

```
bunx --bun shadcn@latest add button --filter=apps/client
```
